        "body": "## Summary\n- Mirror same-surface external final replies into the owning session transcript after dispatcher delivery succeeds.\n- Reuse the existing final-outcome guard so cancelled or failed dispatcher deliveries are not mirrored.\n- Add regression coverage for the Slack same-channel path from #92489.\n\n## Issue\nFixes #92489\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- `pnpm exec vitest run src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --write src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.ts src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.test.ts && git diff --check`\n\nThe new test drives a Slack channel turn where `Provider` matches `OriginatingChannel`, proves the route-reply path is not used, and verifies the delivered assistant reply is appended to `agent:main:slack:channel:C123` with the expected agent id and text.",
